idx.description: A unique row identifier for each sample in the dataset.

Proteomics_Participant_ID.description: A unique identifier assigned to each participant in the proteomics study.

Case_excluded.description: Indicates whether a specific case or participant was excluded from the proteomics analysis.

Proteomics_TMT_batch.description: The identifier for the TMT (Tandem Mass Tag) batch used in the proteomics experiment.

Proteomics_TMT_plex.description: The multiplex level (number of samples combined) within a TMT batch.

Proteomics_TMT_channel.description: Reporter ion channel identifier used in Tandem Mass Tag (TMT) based proteomics quantification.

Proteomics_Parent_Sample_IDs.description: Unique identifier for the parent biological sample from which the proteomics sample was derived.

Proteomics_Aliquot_ID.description: Unique identifier for a specific aliquot of a sample used in a proteomics experiment.

Proteomics_Tumor_Normal.description: Pathological classification or tissue type of the sample, indicating whether it is tumor, normal, or a specific type of normal tissue.

Proteomics_OCT.description: Indicates whether the sample was embedded in Optimal Cutting Temperature (OCT) compound, typically used for cryosectioning.

Country.description: The country of origin or residence of the patient.

Histologic_Grade_FIGO.description: The FIGO (International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics) histologic grade of the tumor, indicating its differentiation level.

Myometrial_invasion_Specify.description: The extent of myometrial invasion by the tumor, specified as a percentage or descriptive category.

Histologic_type.description: The histologic type of the tumor, based on microscopic examination.

Treatment_naive.description: Indicates whether the patient has received any prior treatment for the condition.

Tumor_purity.description: Describes the proportion of tumor cells within a tumor sample, often expressed qualitatively (e.g., high, low) or quantitatively as a percentage.

Path_Stage_Primary_Tumor-pT.description: Pathological primary tumor (pT) staging according to the TNM classification system, indicating the size and extent of the primary tumor.

Path_Stage_Reg_Lymph_Nodes-pN.description: Pathological regional lymph node (pN) staging according to the TNM classification system, indicating the presence and extent of cancer spread to regional lymph nodes.

Clin_Stage_Dist_Mets-cM.description: Clinical distant metastasis (cM) staging according to the TNM classification system, indicating the presence or absence of distant metastasis based on clinical assessment.

Path_Stage_Dist_Mets-pM.description: Pathological distant metastasis (pM) staging according to the TNM classification system, indicating the presence or absence of distant metastasis based on pathological examination.
enum: No pathologic evidence of distant metastasis

tumor_Stage-Pathological.description: Pathological tumor stage, often based on TNM classification, indicating the extent of cancer progression post-surgery.

FIGO_stage.description: FIGO (International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics) stage for gynecological cancers, classifying the disease's extent.

LVSI.description: Lymphovascular space invasion (LVSI) status, indicating the presence or absence of tumor cells in lymphatic or vascular channels.

BMI.description: Body Mass Index (BMI), a measure of body fat based on height and weight, calculated as weight in kilograms divided by the square of height in meters.

Age.description: Age of the patient in years at the time of diagnosis or assessment.

Diabetes.description: Indicates whether a patient has a history of diabetes.

Race.description: The self-identified racial background of the patient.
enum: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander

Ethnicity.description: The self-identified ethnic background of the patient, typically Hispanic or Latino origin.

Gender.description: The self-identified gender of the patient.

Tumor_Site.description: The anatomical location of the primary tumor.

Tumor_Site_Other.description: Free-text description of additional or specific tumor locations not covered by standard site classifications.

Tumor_Focality.description: The number of distinct tumor foci identified, indicating whether the tumor is a single lesion (unifocal) or multiple separate lesions (multifocal).

Tumor_Size_cm.description: The maximum diameter of the primary tumor measured in centimeters.

Estrogen_Receptor.description: The immunohistochemical (IHC) status of estrogen receptor expression in tumor cells, crucial for predicting response to endocrine therapy.

Estrogen_Receptor_%.description: The percentage of tumor cells staining positive for estrogen receptor by immunohistochemistry. This value helps quantify the level of ER expression.

Progesterone_Receptor.description: Status of Progesterone Receptor (PR) protein expression, typically assessed by immunohistochemistry.

Progesterone_Receptor_%.description: Percentage of tumor cells staining positive for Progesterone Receptor (PR) expression. A value of -1 may indicate 'not applicable' or 'undetermined'.

MLH1.description: Expression status of the MLH1 protein, a DNA mismatch repair protein, typically assessed by immunohistochemistry.

MLH2.description: Expression status of the MLH2 protein (likely a typo and refers to MSH2), a DNA mismatch repair protein, typically assessed by immunohistochemistry.

MSH6.description: Expression status of the MSH6 protein, a DNA mismatch repair protein, typically assessed by immunohistochemistry.

PMS2.description: Expression status of the PMS2 protein, often assessed via immunohistochemistry.

p53.description: Expression status of the p53 protein, often assessed via immunohistochemistry.

Other_IHC_specify.description: Detailed specifications or findings from other immunohistochemistry (IHC) markers not captured in specific columns.

MLH1_Promoter_Hypermethylation.description: Status of MLH1 promoter hypermethylation, indicating epigenetic silencing of the MLH1 gene.

Num_full_term_pregnancies.description: The number of full-term pregnancies a patient has had.

EPIC_Bcells.description: Estimated proportion of B cells within a tissue sample, calculated using the EPIC deconvolution algorithm. Values range from 0.0 to 1.0.

EPIC_CAFs.description: Estimated proportion of Cancer-Associated Fibroblasts (CAFs) within a tissue sample, calculated using the EPIC deconvolution algorithm. Values range from 0.0 to 1.0.

EPIC_CD4_Tcells.description: Estimated proportion of CD4+ T cells within a tissue sample, calculated using the EPIC deconvolution algorithm. Values range from 0.0 to 1.0.

EPIC_CD8_Tcells.description: Estimated proportion of CD8+ T cells within a tissue sample, calculated using the EPIC deconvolution algorithm. Values range from 0.0 to 1.0.

EPIC_Endothelial.description: Estimated proportion of Endothelial cells within a tissue sample, calculated using the EPIC deconvolution algorithm. Values range from 0.0 to 1.0.

EPIC_Macrophages.description: Estimated fraction of Macrophages in the sample, derived using the EPIC algorithm. Values range from 0 to 1, representing the proportion of cells.

EPIC_NKcells.description: Estimated fraction of Natural Killer (NK) cells in the sample, derived using the EPIC algorithm. Values range from 0 to 1, representing the proportion of cells.

EPIC_otherCells.description: Estimated fraction of other non-immune cell types in the sample, derived using the EPIC algorithm. Values range from 0 to 1, representing the proportion of cells.

CIBERSORT_B _cells _naive.description: Estimated fraction of naive B cells in the sample, derived using the CIBERSORT algorithm. Values range from 0 to 1, representing the proportion of cells.

CIBERSORT_B _cells _memory.description: Estimated fraction of memory B cells in the sample, derived using the CIBERSORT algorithm. Values range from 0 to 1, representing the proportion of cells.

CIBERSORT_Plasma _cells.description: Fraction or relative abundance of plasma B cells estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD8.description: Fraction or relative abundance of CD8+ T cells estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD4 _naive.description: Fraction or relative abundance of naive CD4+ T cells estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD4 _memory _resting.description: Fraction or relative abundance of resting memory CD4+ T cells estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD4 _memory _activat.description: Fraction or relative abundance of activated memory CD4+ T cells estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _follicular _helper.description: Proportion of T follicular helper cells estimated by CIBERSORT algorithm, reflecting their role in B cell maturation and antibody production.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _regulatory _(Tregs).description: Proportion of T regulatory cells (Tregs) estimated by CIBERSORT algorithm, crucial for immune tolerance and suppressing autoimmune responses.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _gamma _delta.description: Proportion of gamma delta T cells estimated by CIBERSORT algorithm, representing a distinct T cell lineage with innate-like immune functions.

CIBERSORT_NK _cells _resting.description: Proportion of resting Natural Killer (NK) cells estimated by CIBERSORT algorithm, indicating the presence of inactive cytotoxic immune cells.

CIBERSORT_NK _cells _activated.description: Proportion of activated Natural Killer (NK) cells estimated by CIBERSORT algorithm, reflecting the presence of cytotoxic immune cells ready for effector functions.

CIBERSORT_Monocytes.description: Estimated relative abundance of monocytes based on CIBERSORT deconvolution of gene expression data.

CIBERSORT_Macrophages _M0.description: Estimated relative abundance of M0 polarized macrophages based on CIBERSORT deconvolution of gene expression data.

CIBERSORT_Macrophages _M1.description: Estimated relative abundance of M1 polarized macrophages based on CIBERSORT deconvolution of gene expression data.

CIBERSORT_Macrophages _M2.description: Estimated relative abundance of M2 polarized macrophages based on CIBERSORT deconvolution of gene expression data.

CIBERSORT_Dendritic _cells _resting.description: Estimated relative abundance of resting dendritic cells based on CIBERSORT deconvolution of gene expression data.

CIBERSORT_Dendritic _cells _activated.description: Quantifies the estimated fraction of activated dendritic cells in a bulk tissue sample, derived from CIBERSORT deconvolution analysis. Represents an immune cell subset involved in antigen presentation and T-cell activation.

CIBERSORT_Mast _cells _resting.description: Quantifies the estimated fraction of resting mast cells in a bulk tissue sample, derived from CIBERSORT deconvolution analysis. Represents an immune cell subset typically found in tissues, involved in allergic reactions and immune surveillance.

CIBERSORT_Mast _cells _activated.description: Quantifies the estimated fraction of activated mast cells in a bulk tissue sample, derived from CIBERSORT deconvolution analysis. Represents an immune cell subset that has been stimulated and is actively releasing mediators.

CIBERSORT_Eosinophils.description: Quantifies the estimated fraction of eosinophils in a bulk tissue sample, derived from CIBERSORT deconvolution analysis. Represents a type of granulocyte involved in allergic responses and defense against parasites.

CIBERSORT_Neutrophils.description: Quantifies the estimated fraction of neutrophils in a bulk tissue sample, derived from CIBERSORT deconvolution analysis. Represents the most abundant type of granulocyte, crucial for innate immunity and bacterial infection defense.

CIBERSORT_Absolute _score.description: Absolute score reflecting the abundance or fraction of specific immune cell types, derived from gene expression data using the CIBERSORT algorithm. Values typically range between 0 and 1.

ESTIMATE_StromalScore.description: Score quantifying the relative presence of stromal cells within a tumor sample, calculated using the ESTIMATE algorithm based on gene expression data. Higher scores indicate greater stromal infiltration.

ESTIMATE_ImmuneScore.description: Score quantifying the relative presence of immune cells within a tumor sample, calculated using the ESTIMATE algorithm based on gene expression data. Higher scores indicate greater immune infiltration.

ESTIMATE_ESTIMATEScore.description: Overall score derived from the ESTIMATE algorithm, representing the sum of the StromalScore and ImmuneScore. It provides an inverse correlation with tumor purity.

Stemness_score.description: A quantitative score reflecting the degree of stem cell-like characteristics or dedifferentiation in cancer cells, often derived from genomic or transcriptomic data. Values are typically normalized between 0 and 1.

ER_ESR1.description: Expression level or activity score of Estrogen Receptor 1 (ESR1), often related to ER status in breast cancer. Positive values indicate higher expression/activity, negative values lower.

PR_PGR.description: Expression level or activity score of Progesterone Receptor (PGR), often related to PR status in breast cancer. Positive values indicate higher expression/activity, negative values lower.

Pathway_activity_EGFR.description: Activity score for the Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor (EGFR) signaling pathway. Scores typically indicate the level of pathway activation, with positive values for activation and negative for suppression.

Pathway_activity_Hypoxia.description: Activity score for the Hypoxia pathway, reflecting the cellular response to low oxygen conditions. Positive values suggest higher hypoxic activity, negative values suggest lower.

Pathway_activity_JAK.STAT.description: Activity score for the Janus Kinase/Signal Transducers and Activators of Transcription (JAK-STAT) signaling pathway, involved in immunity, cell division, and apoptosis. Positive values indicate higher pathway activation.

Pathway_activity_MAPK.description: Quantification of the activity level of the Mitogen-Activated Protein Kinase (MAPK) signaling pathway, often representing activation or inhibition states.

Pathway_activity_NFkB.description: Quantification of the activity level of the Nuclear Factor Kappa B (NF-kB) signaling pathway, a key regulator of immune responses and inflammation.

Pathway_activity_PI3K.description: Quantification of the activity level of the Phosphoinositide 3-Kinase (PI3K) signaling pathway, critical for cell growth, proliferation, differentiation, and survival.

Pathway_activity_TGFb.description: Quantification of the activity level of the Transforming Growth Factor-beta (TGF-beta) signaling pathway, involved in cell growth, differentiation, apoptosis, and immune regulation.

Pathway_activity_TNFa.description: Quantification of the activity level of the Tumor Necrosis Factor-alpha (TNF-alpha) signaling pathway, a cytokine involved in systemic inflammation and acute phase reactions.

Pathway_activity_Trail.description: Quantified activity score for the TRAIL (TNF-related apoptosis-inducing ligand) pathway, reflecting its activation or inhibition.

Pathway_activity_VEGF.description: Quantified activity score for the VEGF (Vascular Endothelial Growth Factor) pathway, reflecting its activation or inhibition.

Pathway_activity_p53.description: Quantified activity score for the p53 tumor suppressor pathway, reflecting its activation or inhibition.

TP53_ATM.description: Binary indicator for the presence (1) or absence (0) of a genomic alteration (e.g., mutation, deletion) related to the TP53-ATM interaction or pathway.

TP53_CHEK2.description: Binary indicator for the presence (1) or absence (0) of a genomic alteration (e.g., mutation, deletion) related to the TP53-CHEK2 interaction or pathway.

TP53_MDM4.description: Binary indicator for the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic alteration or interaction involving the TP53 and MDM4 genes.

TP53_RPS6KA3.description: Binary indicator for the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic alteration or interaction involving the TP53 and RPS6KA3 genes.

TP53_TP53.description: Binary indicator for the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic alteration within the TP53 gene itself.

TP53_pathway.description: Binary indicator for the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of any significant genomic alteration affecting the TP53 signaling pathway.

PI3K_AKT1.description: Binary indicator for the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic alteration or interaction involving the PI3K pathway and the AKT1 gene.

PI3K_AKT2.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic alteration (e.g., mutation, copy number variation) in the AKT2 gene, a serine/threonine kinase crucial for PI3K signaling.

PI3K_AKT3.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic alteration (e.g., mutation, copy number variation) in the AKT3 gene, another serine/threonine kinase involved in the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_DEPDC5.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic alteration (e.g., mutation, copy number variation) in the DEPDC5 gene, a component of the GATOR1 complex that negatively regulates mTORC1 signaling, which is downstream of PI3K.

PI3K_DEPTOR.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic alteration (e.g., mutation, copy number variation) in the DEPTOR gene, a negative regulator of mTORC1 and mTORC2, crucial for mTOR signaling downstream of PI3K.

PI3K_INPP4B.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic alteration (e.g., mutation, copy number variation) in the INPP4B gene, an inositol polyphosphate-4-phosphatase that negatively regulates the PI3K pathway and acts as a tumor suppressor.

PI3K_MAPKAP1.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of a genomic mutation in the PI3K-MAPKAP1 gene.

PI3K_MLST8.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of a genomic mutation in the PI3K-MLST8 gene.

PI3K_MTOR.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of a genomic mutation in the PI3K-MTOR gene.

PI3K_NPRL2.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of a genomic mutation in the PI3K-NPRL2 gene.

PI3K_NPRL3.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of a genomic mutation in the PI3K-NPRL3 gene.

PI3K_PDK1.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation in the PI3K-PDK1 gene, related to the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_PIK3CA.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation in the PIK3CA gene, a catalytic subunit of PI3K.

PI3K_PIK3CB.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation in the PIK3CB gene, a catalytic subunit of PI3K.

PI3K_PIK3R1.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation in the PIK3R1 gene, a regulatory subunit of PI3K.

PI3K_PIK3R2.description: Indicates the presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation in the PIK3R2 gene, a regulatory subunit of PI3K.

PI3K_PPP2R1A.description: Presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation or alteration in the PPP2R1A gene, a component of the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_PTEN.description: Presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation or alteration in the PTEN gene, a tumor suppressor involved in the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_RHEB.description: Presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation or alteration in the RHEB gene, an activator of mTOR downstream of the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_RICTOR.description: Presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation or alteration in the RICTOR gene, a component of mTORC2, involved in the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_RPS6.description: Presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a genomic mutation or alteration in the RPS6 gene, a ribosomal protein downstream of the PI3K/mTOR pathway.

PI3K_RPS6KB1.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of an alteration or mutational status in the RPS6KB1 gene, a component of the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_RPTOR.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of an alteration or mutational status in the RPTOR gene, a component of the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_STK11.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of an alteration or mutational status in the STK11 gene, a component of the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_TSC1.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of an alteration or mutational status in the TSC1 gene, a component of the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_TSC2.description: Indicates the presence (1) or absence (0) of an alteration or mutational status in the TSC2 gene, a component of the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_pathway.description: Indicates the status or activity of the PI3K signaling pathway, often represented as 0 for inactive/wild-type or 1 for active/mutated.

HRD_BRCA1.description: Indicates the presence of Homologous Recombination Deficiency (HRD) associated with a BRCA1 mutation, typically 0 for absence and 1 for presence.

HRD_BRCA2.description: Indicates the presence of Homologous Recombination Deficiency (HRD) associated with a BRCA2 mutation, typically 0 for absence and 1 for presence.

HRD_BRCA1_or_BRCA2.description: Indicates the presence of Homologous Recombination Deficiency (HRD) associated with either a BRCA1 or BRCA2 mutation, typically 0 for absence and 1 for presence.

CNV_DEL.description: A quantitative score or metric representing the magnitude or frequency of copy number variation (CNV) deletion events.

CNV_AMP.description: The amplitude or magnitude of a Copy Number Variation (CNV) event.

CNV_class.description: Categorical classification of the Copy Number Variation (CNV) status.

CNV_idx.description: A calculated index or score quantifying Copy Number Variation (CNV).

CNV_1q_DEL.description: Score indicating deletion presence and severity at chromosome arm 1q, part of Copy Number Variation analysis.

CNV_3q_DEL.description: Score indicating deletion presence and severity at chromosome arm 3q, part of Copy Number Variation analysis.

CNV_4q_DEL.description: Copy number variation deletion on chromosome 4, q arm, typically represented as a log2 ratio.

CNV_1q_AMP.description: Copy number variation amplification on chromosome 1, q arm, typically represented as a log2 ratio.

CNV_3q_AMP.description: Copy number variation amplification on chromosome 3, q arm, typically represented as a log2 ratio.

CNV_4q_AMP.description: Copy number variation amplification on chromosome 4, q arm, typically represented as a log2 ratio.

Purity_Immune.description: Immune cell infiltration purity score, representing the proportion of immune cells in a sample.

Purity_Cancer.description: Fractional purity of cancer cells within a tumor sample.

Purity_Stroma.description: Fractional purity of stromal cells within a tumor sample.

MSI_status.description: Microsatellite instability status, indicating a defective DNA mismatch repair system in a tumor.

POLE_subtype.description: Indicates the presence of pathogenic mutations in the POLE gene, often associated with an ultrarmutated phenotype.

JAK1_MS_INDEL.description: Status of microsatellite insertions or deletions (indels) in the JAK1 gene, relevant for genomic mutation analysis.

JAK1_Mutation.description: Mutation status of the JAK1 gene.

Log2_variant_per_Mbp.description: Log2-transformed count of all genetic variants (SNPs and INDELs) per megabase pair (Mbp), often used as a measure of tumor mutational burden (TMB).

Log2_SNP_per_Mbp.description: Log2-transformed count of single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) per megabase pair (Mbp).

Log2_INDEL_per_Mbp.description: Log2-transformed count of insertions or deletions (INDELs) per megabase pair (Mbp).

Log2_variant_total.description: Log2-transformed total count of all genetic variants (SNPs and INDELs) across the sequenced genome.

Log2_SNP_total.description: Log2 transformed total count or frequency of Single Nucleotide Polymorphisms (SNPs) detected in the sample.

Log2_INDEL_total.description: Log2 transformed total count or frequency of Insertions/Deletions (INDELs) detected in the sample.

Genomics_subtype.description: Genomic subtype classification of the tumor or sample, often indicative of specific molecular characteristics or pathways.

Mutation_signature_C>A.description: The score or frequency representing the contribution of the C>A (Cytosine to Adenine) transversion mutation signature, often associated with specific mutational processes.

Mutation_signature_C>G.description: The score or frequency representing the contribution of the C>G (Cytosine to Guanine) transversion mutation signature, often associated with specific mutational processes.

Mutation_signature_C>T.description: The percentage or frequency of C>T mutations contributing to a mutation signature.

Mutation_signature_T>C.description: The percentage or frequency of T>C mutations contributing to a mutation signature.

Mutation_signature_T>A.description: The percentage or frequency of T>A mutations contributing to a mutation signature.

Mutation_signature_T>G.description: The percentage or frequency of T>G mutations contributing to a mutation signature.

WXS_normal_sample_type.description: The type of normal sample used for Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) analysis.

WXS_normal_filename.description: Filename of the normal Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) sample.

WXS_normal_UUID.description: Unique Universal Identifier (UUID) for the normal Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) sample.

WXS_tumor_sample_type.description: Type of the tumor sample associated with Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS).

WXS_tumor_filename.description: Filename of the tumor Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) sample.

WXS_tumor_UUID.description: Unique Universal Identifier (UUID) for the tumor Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) sample.

WGS_normal_sample_type.description: Type of sample collected for Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS) for the normal comparison.

WGS_normal_UUID.description: Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the normal sample used in Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS).

WGS_tumor_sample_type.description: Type of sample collected for Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS) for the tumor.

WGS_tumor_UUID.description: Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the tumor sample used in Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS).

RNAseq_R1_sample_type.description: Type of sample collected for RNA Sequencing (RNAseq) for the first replicate (R1).

RNAseq_R1_filename.description: The filename for the first read (R1) of RNA sequencing data, typically in FASTQ.gz format.

RNAseq_R1_UUID.description: A Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) assigned to the RNA sequencing first read (R1) file.

RNAseq_R2_sample_type.description: The biological sample type from which the RNA sequencing data (R2) was derived.

RNAseq_R2_filename.description: The filename for the second read (R2) of RNA sequencing data, typically in FASTQ.gz format.

RNAseq_R2_UUID.description: A Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) assigned to the RNA sequencing second read (R2) file.

miRNAseq_sample_type.description: Type of sample from which the miRNA sequencing data was derived.

miRNAseq_UUID.description: Unique identifier (UUID) for the miRNA sequencing sample.

Methylation_available.description: Indicates whether methylation data is available for the sample.

Methylation_quality.description: Quality assessment of the methylation data for the sample.
